Brazil Coffee Exports Rise 15 Percent in June, Ministry Says

-- B y   L u c i a   K a s s a i
-- 
2011-07-01T19:26:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-01/brazil-coffee-exports-rise-15-percent-in-june-ministry-says.html
Coffee exports from  Brazil , the
world’s largest producer, jumped 15 percent last month from a
year earlier, Brazil’s Trade Ministry said.  Brazil shipped 2.2 million bags in June, up from 1.92
million a year ago, the ministry said today in a report posted
on its website.  A bag of coffee weighs 60 kilograms.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lucia Kassai in  Sao Paulo  at 
 lkassai@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dale Crofts at   dcrofts@bloomberg.net . 